The properties of the lubricating fluid in the gap between the disc and the immobile electrode have a high impact on the efficiency of the device. The fluid’s electrical properties, i.e., its screening length and dielectric constant greatly affect the values of Cmin\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
