To increase the maximum capacitance for a molecular liquid, it is imperative to use a liquid with a high-dielectric constant along with a gap that is as narrow as possible, i.e., in the nm range. We consider here two different high-dielectric and nonvolatile molecular liquids: formamide, of bulk dielectric constant26ϵ=111\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
